Resource Profile: Condensed Assay Task

Official URL: https://nih-ncpi.github.io/ncpi-fhir-ig-2/StructureDefinition/ncpi-assay-task Version: 0.2.0
Draft as of 2025-08-12 Computable Name: NcpiAssayTask

Profile to represent informatics assay definitions within NCPI, such as Submitted Data, WGS, RNA-seq, etc. A single resource to represent the intent, execution, and results of a research assay.

Usages:

  • Examples for this Profile: Task/t1 and Task/t2

You can also check for usages in the FHIR IG Statistics

: contained.where((('#'+id in (%resource.descendants().reference | %resource.descendants().as(canonical) | %resource.descendants().as(uri) | %resource.descendants().as(url))) or descendants().where(reference = '#').exists() or descendants().where(as(canonical) = '#').exists() or descendants().where(as(canonical) = '#').exists()).not()).trace('unmatched', id).empty()
dom-4errorTaskIf a resource is contained in another resource, it SHALL NOT have a meta.versionId or a meta.lastUpdated
: contained.meta.versionId.empty() and contained.meta.lastUpdated.empty()
